Tobi Aworinde Vice President Yemi Osinbajo and his wife, Dolapo, have expressed their condolences to the President, Major General Muhammadu Buhari (retd), and the family of the Chief of Staff to the President, Abba Kyari, over the senior presidential aide’s death. The Vice President, in a statement by his Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity, Laolu Akande, said, “Dolapo and I express our sympathies to the President, Mrs Kulu Kyari, the children, and members of the family on the passing of the late Mallam Abba Kyari, Chief of Staff to the President.” The First Lady, Mrs Aisha Buhari, also expressed her sympathy to the family of the Kyari. Mrs Buhari, in a statement, said, “From God Almighty we came and to Him we shall return. I condole with Mrs Kulu Abba Kyari and the entire family of the late Mallam Abba Kyari over the death of their husband and father. “While wishing all those infected a speedy recovery, I pray for an end to the COVID-19 pandemic.” Copyright PUNCH.
